        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 22 at 2:51PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 251 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Spring Hill, or 11 miles east of Midway, moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Midway, Comer, Barbour County Public Lake Dam, Spring Hill, Mount
Andrew, and Batesville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
